author: sussman
msg: Okay, I've been secretly sitting on this for over a week, just a
little experiment.  Thought I'd commit it for everyone's amusement.
Try this with a local repository:  'svnadmin shell repos', and then
* svnadmin.h:  new header file.  contains #includes that were in main.c.
* main.c:      move #includes to svnadmin.h;  add new "shell" subcommand.
* shell.c:     implement a simple, exploratory shell.

author: kevin
msg: Rename the `ancestor' part of an entry to `url'.  Note that this may not
change all appropriate comments, or variable/argument names.  These should
be looked specifically in include/svn_wc.h, libsvn_wc/wc.h, and
(svn_wc__atts_to_entries): replace ancestor field with url field.
(resolve_to_defaults): Replace ancestor field with url field, and use
SVN_ERR_WC_MISSING_URL instead of SVN_ERR_WC_MISSING_ANCESTRY if not
use url field instead of ancestor field.
(write_entry): Keep comments in sync with ancestor->url rename, use
SVN_WC_ENTRY_ATTR_URL instead of SVN_WC_ENTRY_ATTR_ANCESTOR, and rename
replace the ancestor field with url fields in svn_wc_entry_t references.
(svn_wc_is_wc_root): Use the url field instead of the ancestor field.
(svn_client_log): Use entry->url instead of entry->ancestor.  If it's not
there, use SVN_ERR_WC_MISSING_URL instead of SVN_ERR_WC_MISSING_ANCESTRY.
